    "details": "https://www.postgresql.org/support/security/CVE-2025-12818/ reports:\n\n> - Integer wraparound in multiple PostgreSQL libpq client library\n>   functions allows an application input provider or network peer to\n>   cause libpq to undersize an allocation and write out-of-bounds by\n>   hundreds of megabytes. This results in a segmentation fault for the\n>   application using libpq.\n> - Missing authorization in PostgreSQL CREATE STATISTICS command allows\n>   a table owner to achieve denial of service against other CREATE\n>   STATISTICS users by creating in any schema. A later CREATE\n>   STATISTICS for the same name, from a user having the CREATE\n>   privilege, would then fail.\n",
